    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "284bc29d_f7f6b7a8",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 59,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-24T16:43:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it would be useful to make an interface for specs.TempGitRepo, e.g.:\n\ntype Checkouter interface {\n  Checkout(rs db.RepoState) (*git.TempCheckout, error)\n}\nand pass this in to TaskScheduler. You can then easily mock it instead of downloading all of depot_tools for each TS test and parsing command lines in tests. Also, it will be easier to think about more complex implementations (e.g. worker pools) if TempGitRepo is an interface rather than a function.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 59,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "cdf15d7965a890ba8f8cef877d9a71d3b9e3fbaf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b11905b6_1069bedc",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 59,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-24T18:38:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How would this work?  In most cases we\u0027d still need to end up with an actual checkout, or else whatever we\u0027re using it for will fail.  With the updates in the last CL, we can now easily create RepoStates which can be synced, including Gerrit CLs, so there\u0027s not as much need for mocking, except maybe for speeding up the test.",
      "revId": "cdf15d7965a890ba8f8cef877d9a71d3b9e3fbaf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
